NAME
    gcloud beta tasks queues pause - pause a queue

SYNOPSIS
    gcloud beta tasks queues pause QUEUE [GCLOUD_WIDE_FLAG ...]

DESCRIPTION
    (BETA) If a queue is paused then the system will stop executing the tasks
    in the queue until it is resumed. Tasks can still be added when the queue
    is paused.

POSITIONAL ARGUMENTS
     QUEUE
        The queue to pause.

GCLOUD WIDE FLAGS
    These flags are available to all commands: --account, --billing-project,
    --configuration, --flags-file, --flatten, --format, --help,
    --impersonate-service-account, --log-http, --project, --quiet,
    --trace-token, --user-output-enabled, --verbosity. Run $ gcloud help for
    details.

EXAMPLES
    To pause a queue:

        $ gcloud beta tasks queues pause my-queue

NOTES
    This command is currently in BETA and may change without notice. These
    variants are also available:

        $ gcloud tasks queues pause
        $ gcloud alpha tasks queues pause

